org.hl7.util
Class ForwardReferenceTool<V>

java.lang.Object
  org.hl7.util.ForwardReferenceTool<V>

public class ForwardReferenceTool<V>
extends java.lang.Object

This class deals with forward references that can happen in any symbol-table driven structure. It is so general it can be used with any map. This is used as follows: suppose you have a Map map and you want to resolve String name. Then you do this:

ForwardReferenceTool.get(map, name, Thing.class, new ForwardReferenceTool.Replacer() { public void replace(Thing value) { _value = value; } });

And suppose you are defining a new Thing value under that name, then you do this:

ForwardReferenceTool.put(map, name, value);

Author:
Gunther Schadow
